$$
IS = g*MS{\left( {HR} \right)} + {\left( {1 - g} \right)}*AT{\left( {HR} \right)}
$$\end{document}in which MS describes the amount of movement of the coronary artery as a function of heart rate, AT describes the acquisition time as a function of heart rate and g is a weight factor.

